<subSubSection id="C30198A6FFF1FFC9FF02FCAAFECA7047" pageId="13" pageNumber="126" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA4CB2DFFF1FFC9FF02FCAAFF257626" blockId="13.[131,776,822,1327]" box="[132,207,822,848]" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">NOTES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA4CB2DFFF1FFC9FF02FCCAFECA7047" blockId="13.[131,776,822,1327]" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AB6DCFFF1FFC9FF02FCCAFE9C7618" author="LECOMTE H." box="[132,374,853,880]" pageId="13" pageNumber="126" refId="ref13254" refString="LECOMTE H. 1925. - Les Bois de l'Indochine. Agence economique de l'Indochine, Paris, 312 p." type="book" year="1925">Lecomte (1925: 189)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF1FFC9FE47FCC9FDBE7618" box="[449,596,853,880]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">Poilane 2782</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF1FFC9FD09FCC9FD237607" box="[655,713,853,879]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">6869</emphasis>
from Nhatrang and 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF1FFC9FEA8FCE9FE2B76F8" box="[302,449,885,912]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">Poilane 9872</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF1FFC9FE7BFCEAFDDD76F8" box="[509,567,886,912]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">9723</emphasis>
from Phanrang as the original material. Later, he described 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BB0AEFFF1FFC9FDDDFC0AFE9E76A7" authority="Lecomte (1928 a: 114)" authorityName="Lecomte, Notulae Systematicae" authorityPageNumber="114" authorityYear="1928" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="13" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="finetii">
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF1FFC9FDDDFC0AFCE276C7" box="[603,776,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">Diospyros finetii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AB6DCFFF1FFC9FF02FC2AFE9E76A7" author="LECOMTE H." box="[132,372,949,976]" pageId="13" pageNumber="126" pagination="99 - 121" refId="ref13173" refString="LECOMTE H. 1928 a. - Ebenacees nouvelles de l'Indochine. Notulae Systematicae 4 (4): 99 - 121. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 6463259" type="journal article" year="1928">Lecomte (1928a: 114)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
based on the same collections, except 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF1FFC9FF02FC49FEE47687" box="[132,270,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">Poilane 9872</emphasis>
which he no longer cited as one of the relevant specimens and appears to be lost. As there appears to be no reason why Lecomte rejected the earlier epithet, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BB0AEFFF1FFC9FD09FB8AFD057147" authorityName="Lecomte, Notulae Systematicae" authorityYear="1928" box="[655,751,1045,1071]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="13" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="finetii">
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF1FFC9FD09FB8AFD057147" box="[655,751,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">D. finetii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a superfluous name, homotypic with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BB0AEFFF1FFC9FDA5FBAAFD717127" box="[547,667,1077,1103]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="13" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nitidula">
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF1FFC9FDA5FBAAFD717127" box="[547,667,1077,1103]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">D. nitidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Three of the cited collections have been located at NY, P and VNM, but we could not find 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF1FFC9FEFEFBE8FDE971E7" box="[376,515,1140,1167]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">Poilane 9872</emphasis>
. Here, we designate the specimen P00721683 from 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF1FFC9FE2AFB08FDDC71C7" box="[428,566,1172,1199]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">Poilane 2782</emphasis>
as the 
<typeStatus id="54A0758FFFF1FFC9FDF8FB08FD0A71C6" box="[638,736,1172,1198]" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">lectotype</typeStatus>
because it is the best preserved out of the only two sheets across the three gatherings to have been determined by Lecomte as a type of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BB0AEFFF1FFC9FF76FB69FEB97066" authorityName="Lecomte, Notulae Systematicae" authorityYear="1928" box="[240,339,1268,1294]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="13" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="finetii">
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF1FFC9FF76FB69FEB97066" box="[240,339,1268,1294]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">D. finetii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the other being VNM00015247 from 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF1FFC9FF00FA88FEFA7046" box="[134,272,1300,1326]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="126">Poilane 6869</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
